"$500 for the death of Charlie Wei."

01:13.447 --> 01:15.614
Hey, friend. Not bad style.

01:17.326 --> 01:19.327
You should take it easy. You look done in.

01:22.126 --> 01:24.726
Guess you must be
the four-door fist champion.

01:26.125 --> 01:27.259
Charlie Wei?

01:28.445 --> 01:30.945
I'm Charlie Wei.
Your name, if you have one.

01:32.205 --> 01:33.405
Sure, it's Thunderleg.

01:36.725 --> 01:38.792
I've heard of his devil's kick.
Of course, yeah.

01:39.284 --> 01:40.884
Everyone knows in the kung fu world.

01:41.284 --> 01:43.218
It's a method that's
never been defeated yet.

01:44.804 --> 01:46.071
And won't be.

01:47.524 --> 01:49.357
I suppose I should warn you:

01:49.924 --> 01:52.091
I've been given good money to kill you.

01:53.043 --> 01:55.677
What the hell are you talking about?
Someone's paid you to kill me?

01:56.282 --> 01:58.349
I'll give you twice as much to kill him!

01:59.442 --> 02:01.809
You could, only my honour comes first.

02:02.843 --> 02:05.710
You must realize I'm paid to kill.
The contract's sealed.

02:06.362 --> 02:08.162
- So you must die.
- Don't be so sure of that...

02:08.601 --> 02:10.735
...for Charlie Wei,
champion of the four-door fist...

02:11.241 --> 02:12.841
...has never yet been defeated.

02:13.961 --> 02:16.028
I'll break every bone in your body...

02:16.681 --> 02:17.981
...and send you to hell.

03:38.033 --> 03:39.300
Professor?

03:42.032 --> 03:43.966
- What is it, master?
- You'll finish the lesson.

03:44.512 --> 03:46.813
- I have something to attend to.
- Yes, sir. I will, sir.

03:54.312 --> 03:55.179
Stop!

03:57.551 --> 03:59.051
I'm now going to demonstrate.

04:00.151 --> 04:02.251
The first lesson I will instruct you in...

04:02.751 --> 04:04.418
...is the 5 animal styles.
- He's gone bonkers.

04:04.830 --> 04:06.564
- Three-legged cat.
- Four-eyed rat.

04:07.591 --> 04:08.724
Let's get started.

04:10.230 --> 04:11.563
Dragon sees tiger.

04:12.990 --> 04:15.457
Tiger tears. Snake's tongue darts out.

04:17.149 --> 04:20.249
Panther sees fire.
White crane spreads wings.

04:21.909 --> 04:23.643
No, hold it, hold it.

04:26.749 --> 04:29.816
There isn't any power in your wrist.
How do you expect to make progress?

04:30.629 --> 04:31.495
Well?

04:48.026 --> 04:49.393
Straighten it up.

05:06.625 --> 05:09.425
I suppose you think that was real funny,
pulling tricks on your teacher.

05:10.064 --> 05:12.231
We'll see. Take that! And that!

05:12.744 --> 05:15.144
- It wasn't me!
- Who was it? Tell me.

05:16.103 --> 05:17.037
Who was it?

05:17.303 --> 05:18.337
Freddie did it.

05:24.583 --> 05:25.983
So, Freddie Wong.

05:26.983 --> 05:29.250
Now, just because your father is
Master Wong...

05:29.782 --> 05:32.183
...gives you no damn right
to cause any trouble here.

05:32.742 --> 05:35.243
Oh, balls.
Who told you kung fu is just a good start?

05:35.821 --> 05:38.755
So that's it.
You mean to say my kung fu is lousy?

05:39.621 --> 05:41.688
It's not as bad as that,
but it isn't the greatest.

05:42.661 --> 05:45.161
Suppose you show me
exactly what's wrong with it.

05:46.261 --> 05:48.495
Right. Just take a look
at your panther sees fire.

05:49.020 --> 05:51.521
- What's wrong with it?
- Look at that spread between your paws.

05:52.141 --> 05:53.674
That's an open invite.

05:54.220 --> 05:56.520
And that horse's stance
is completely bowlegged.

05:57.060 --> 05:58.327
I bet on one sweep that I...

06:02.059 --> 06:03.826
There, you've been thrown, yeah?

06:04.299 --> 06:05.266
Just wait.

06:14.858 --> 06:16.858
Shut up! Shut up, you turkeys!

06:20.937 --> 06:23.204
You'd like to test your teacher's kung fu,
would you?

06:23.738 --> 06:25.738
And magpies can't fly, can they?

06:27.817 --> 06:30.651
I can stand almost anything, you bum!

06:31.296 --> 06:33.330
But I've taken enough of this bullshit.

06:33.816 --> 06:34.917
Right. Come on!

06:41.415 --> 06:43.216
You're wide open.
Do you know that, teacher?

06:43.655 --> 06:44.389
What?

07:06.533 --> 07:08.233
See how good his horse stance is?

07:10.693 --> 07:11.993
Potbelly! Shut up!

07:19.892 --> 07:21.159
Look, right foot.

07:23.972 --> 07:25.438
Cheat, cheat, cheat!

07:25.811 --> 07:26.811
Bastard!

07:28.171 --> 07:29.071
Fresh roosters.

07:29.331 --> 07:30.598
Get your fresh roosters here.

07:32.730 --> 07:34.797
You know, Freddie? You're the cat's ass...

07:35.290 --> 07:37.023
...making old crow face dance like that.

07:37.450 --> 07:39.117
He's always so full of bullshit.

07:39.530 --> 07:42.230
He thinks he's God's gift to kung fu.
Just to see him makes me puke.

07:42.850 --> 07:45.617
- You sure made him dance.
- You should have seen his face.

07:46.650 --> 07:49.717
You sure did all of us a favour,
that's for sure.

07:53.209 --> 07:55.542
- That's not bad.
- So have some more then.

07:56.128 --> 07:58.562
Dumbhead.
I was talking about that chick there.

08:00.008 --> 08:02.475
That perfect frame she's got. Sexy!

08:04.087 --> 08:05.354
- How much?
- That one is 76.

08:05.688 --> 08:07.121
You mean that one in the red?

08:07.487 --> 08:10.021
Imagine what it'd be like
to be kissed by that chick.

08:10.607 --> 08:12.374
Kissing her is for children.

08:12.807 --> 08:14.374
I could get that broad to hug me.

08:14.766 --> 08:17.266
- Come on!
- She wouldn't.

08:17.846 --> 08:20.146
- You wanna bet on it?
- I'll bet you a whole dinner.

08:20.686 --> 08:24.186
She's hot, that kind.
She won't even take a second look at you.

08:24.966 --> 08:26.500
- Come on.
- All right.

08:26.885 --> 08:28.419
A whole dinner then.

08:33.485 --> 08:34.385
Watch.

08:35.605 --> 08:37.238
He's in for trouble.

08:44.324 --> 08:45.624
- What is it?
- It's agony!

08:45.964 --> 08:47.764
- Something's in my eye.
- What's the matter?

08:48.204 --> 08:50.937
Blow it out, please. Can't you help me?

08:51.563 --> 08:52.563
Can you?

08:54.124 --> 08:55.424
One more, huh?

08:56.883 --> 08:58.483
- He did it!
- Did you see that?

08:58.883 --> 09:01.016
Thanks a lot. Hey, a snake! There!

09:03.962 --> 09:06.463
It's all right. Don't be scared. I'll kill it.

09:07.041 --> 09:08.841
- That's a technique.
- Sure is.

09:09.281 --> 09:11.881
I gotta try that on your sister.

09:12.481 --> 09:13.848
On my sister?

09:17.441 --> 09:20.208
Thought you could come fresh
with my daughter, did you?

09:23.361 --> 09:27.028
Me, touch her? She was asking for it.
Dumb bitch.

09:28.799 --> 09:31.133
Don't deny it.
You just wanted to lay your filthy hands...

09:31.719 --> 09:34.653
On her? That's a laugh.
She's much too ugly for that.

09:35.719 --> 09:37.252
Think you're real smart, huh?

09:37.639 --> 09:39.272
I'll teach you a lesson, boy.

09:50.277 --> 09:52.111
So, you want to play at kung fu.

09:52.557 --> 09:53.657
Try this!

10:04.956 --> 10:07.456
- She's not joking.
- The old bitch is tough.

10:11.675 --> 10:13.575
Hey, guys, you gotta help me.

10:16.115 --> 10:17.648
Some friends they make.

10:30.994 --> 10:33.661
You're nothing but a skinny old woman,
so I'll let you win.

10:44.552 --> 10:45.786
Fresh peas. Fresh...

10:46.393 --> 10:47.459
Son of a...

10:49.752 --> 10:52.352
What's your game?
Stumbling about like some drunken stooge.

10:52.952 --> 10:54.185
Don't answer back there.

10:54.992 --> 10:56.159
Hey, Jerry!

10:56.752 --> 10:58.252
Come, who'll buy?

11:00.270 --> 11:01.937
See, mister. Jade antique.

11:04.951 --> 11:06.484
- Is it real?
- But of course, sir.

11:06.870 --> 11:09.203
It's an heirloom, mister.
It's worth money, sir.

11:10.230 --> 11:12.264
- How much is it?
- $10.

11:12.749 --> 11:15.050
That's very expensive. Come.

11:16.429 --> 11:19.230
- Here.
- Just 10 cents?

11:21.989 --> 11:23.823
- Mister, you can't give me this.
- Hands off!

11:24.268 --> 11:25.668
This wouldn't buy an old plate.

11:26.028 --> 11:28.295
I couldn't sell such a valuable piece
for only 10 cents.

11:28.828 --> 11:30.928
You don't want to sell,
you give me my money back.

11:31.428 --> 11:32.561
But my jade!

11:35.108 --> 11:37.008
That was all I had in the world, sir.
Pay for it!

11:37.467 --> 11:39.434
You expect payment from me? Take this!

11:40.827 --> 11:42.360
Daddy, are you all right?

11:42.747 --> 11:44.814
Please, at least give me something.

11:45.306 --> 11:46.140
Sure.

11:46.427 --> 11:48.127
Daddy! Daddy!

11:49.306 --> 11:50.706
What's wrong, old man?

11:51.066 --> 11:52.999
He smashed my jade, and he won't pay.

11:57.305 --> 11:58.772
Shithead. Piss off.

11:59.785 --> 12:02.486
- Think you're talking to your mother?
- I'll see you rot in hell!

12:05.345 --> 12:06.912
You'd better hand over this man's money.

12:07.305 --> 12:07.971
Pay?

12:08.184 --> 12:09.851
Not before I put you in the ground.

12:10.265 --> 12:12.031
It's too bad you feel that way. Know why?

12:12.464 --> 12:15.964
There's nothing been going right today,
so you caught me in a bad mood.

12:17.184 --> 12:19.484
Now, I'm gonna have to teach you
how to pay.

12:50.301 --> 12:51.667
You're mad, huh?

13:04.219 --> 13:05.485
You almost killed me!

13:16.218 --> 13:17.785
My knuckles were barely missed.

13:25.936 --> 13:28.003
- This is for you. Now get going!
- Thank you, sir.

13:40.655 --> 13:42.756
That's enough. I'm dying.

13:43.455 --> 13:45.622
Don't worry. You're safe.
It's only the blunt side.

13:49.655 --> 13:51.455
I have no intention of killing you...

13:51.895 --> 13:53.028
...yet.

13:58.814 --> 13:59.948
Please!

14:01.893 --> 14:03.960
- That one really came close.
- I beg of you!

14:04.454 --> 14:05.987
And watch what you're doing.

14:07.933 --> 14:09.233
Drop dead.

14:11.292 --> 14:14.059
Now, begin to dance to my tune,
or I'll make you sing for supper.

14:19.612 --> 14:21.479
You're fortunate
because it seems I do miss...

14:21.932 --> 14:23.599
...although it's quite by accident.

14:24.011 --> 14:25.078
Oh, please!

14:27.171 --> 14:29.104
I chop, chop, chop this meat.

14:29.571 --> 14:31.471
So then I slice, slice, slice.

14:31.931 --> 14:34.698
And then I beat, beat, beat.
Mix it all together!

14:35.331 --> 14:37.231
It sure has brightened the day I met you.

14:44.809 --> 14:46.876
You know this? It must be at least...

14:47.609 --> 14:49.476
...10 years, brother,
since we've seen each other.

14:49.930 --> 14:51.896
And you hardly look a day older.

14:52.689 --> 14:54.656
I would not have recognized my niece.

14:55.689 --> 14:56.856
She isn't a bad girl...

14:57.168 --> 14:59.202
...just a bit naive.

14:59.848 --> 15:02.215
- And where is Freddie?
- That young rascal.

15:02.768 --> 15:05.468
He's a handful. Always out with his pals,
getting into trouble.

15:06.088 --> 15:08.221
Very grown up now.
You won't recognize him.

15:08.728 --> 15:10.861
By the way, you'll stay for a few days?

15:12.767 --> 15:13.600
Freddie.

15:14.447 --> 15:16.347
I say, Freddie, come and meet your aunt.

15:20.046 --> 15:23.046
- Come on, lad.
- I'll... Coming.

15:32.485 --> 15:33.518
Say hello.

15:34.845 --> 15:36.545
Hello, Auntie, cousin.

15:36.964 --> 15:38.631
- Hello.
- Hello, Freddie.

15:39.125 --> 15:40.158
What on earth's the matter?

15:40.445 --> 15:42.845
I seem to have pulled a muscle in my neck.

15:43.404 --> 15:45.871
I'll soon put that right.
Here, let your aunt fix that.

15:46.443 --> 15:49.077
- I'll be all right.
- Relax just for a second.

15:51.643 --> 15:52.510
Oh, dear.

15:54.203 --> 15:55.236
Oh, Mother.

15:56.523 --> 15:58.557
- Well, you feel better?
- Thank you, yes.

16:01.842 --> 16:02.909
Be all right now.

16:03.482 --> 16:06.249
Your son's grown
into a real smart-looking fellow.

16:06.922 --> 16:09.722
Yes, he's quite clever.
Also, his kung fu's not bad.

16:10.881 --> 16:14.081
Oh? I should like to see
his kung fu sometime.

16:15.001 --> 16:17.101
All right. You would enjoy a match.

16:17.761 --> 16:19.861
I believe that you are strict with him,
from all accounts.

16:20.361 --> 16:22.361
I've heard he's regarded highly
in the neighbourhood.

16:22.841 --> 16:24.407
That's a fact? Tell me what they say.

16:24.920 --> 16:26.987
They've said
that he's courteous and polite...

16:27.480 --> 16:29.913
...setting other boys a good example,
well-mannered.

16:31.919 --> 16:34.853
That makes me really proud
to be his father. Come here, son.

16:42.398 --> 16:44.898
I'm so glad he isn't like the other boys
around here.

16:45.478 --> 16:47.112
They're real sex maniacs.

16:47.838 --> 16:48.938
That's right. Only today...

16:49.238 --> 16:51.905
...my own daughter
was attacked by one of them.

16:52.517 --> 16:56.084
Besides that, when I went to rescue her,
he even attacked me.

16:57.917 --> 17:01.117
You mean to tell me both of you
were attacked here in my own town?

17:02.037 --> 17:03.603
Would you recognize him?

17:06.156 --> 17:08.756
As if I could forget. Yes, I'd recognize him.

17:09.515 --> 17:11.882
And when I find him,
I'll flay the skin off his back.

17:12.435 --> 17:14.135
Freddie, come along.

17:15.236 --> 17:17.469
- Uncle, there's really no need.
- But why?

17:17.994 --> 17:20.428
Because he's in this very room
standing quite near us.

17:21.273 --> 17:23.175
- But where?
- Standing right over there.

17:23.714 --> 17:24.981
Your precious son Freddie.

17:28.314 --> 17:29.114
What?

17:30.674 --> 17:31.607
It can't...

17:36.154 --> 17:37.554
Down on your knees!

17:38.034 --> 17:38.900
Please!

17:39.153 --> 17:41.887
You'll pay for this, you scum, you criminal!

17:49.232 --> 17:50.399
Oh, my gosh.

18:02.230 --> 18:03.064
Robert Wong.

18:03.310 --> 18:05.310
Yes, Mr. Lee. What has happened?

18:06.630 --> 18:09.564
I'll tell you what.
That bastard son of yours beat him up!

18:12.750 --> 18:14.083
Why should he do that?

18:14.430 --> 18:17.364
Because he's nothing but a wild animal.
Viciously attacked my son...

18:18.029 --> 18:20.529
...breaking his legs, arms,
and the poor boy's skull.

18:23.349 --> 18:25.516
Oh, my. He really beat him up.

18:26.029 --> 18:29.729
- He looks like a dumpling.
- Well, what are you going to do?

18:32.148 --> 18:32.948
Father!

18:33.428 --> 18:35.395
You vermin from hell!
I'll beat you to death!

18:35.867 --> 18:37.001
Please, Father!

18:38.467 --> 18:39.901
Brother, you musn't kill your own son.

18:40.267 --> 18:42.601
Yes! I've got to kill this devil.

18:43.147 --> 18:44.713
He's a disgrace to the name of Wong.

18:45.626 --> 18:47.460
Sounds bad
for a teacher of your standing...

18:47.907 --> 18:49.574
...to flog his own son to death.

18:50.627 --> 18:52.793
If he's got to be punished, I suggest that...

18:53.786 --> 18:56.286
...Mr. Lee here is quite capable.

18:59.625 --> 19:00.625
Stop him!

19:01.985 --> 19:04.552
It was your son I beat,
so let him punish me.

19:05.344 --> 19:06.778
There.

19:07.265 --> 19:09.532
Now, you hit me.
I promise I won't fight back.

19:11.744 --> 19:13.244
So you're funny, huh?

19:13.984 --> 19:16.218
All right, Mr. Wong.
What are you gonna do?

19:17.264 --> 19:19.764
As from this moment, I disown him.

19:20.344 --> 19:22.211
This slime is no longer mine.

19:22.663 --> 19:23.997
Do what you like with him.

19:26.222 --> 19:28.356
So my suggestion: You pick your man.

19:29.023 --> 19:31.590
He'll fight Freddie,
who'll be strictly forbidden to fight back.

19:32.223 --> 19:33.823
Ten strokes should be enough.

19:34.302 --> 19:36.636
Now, Mr. Lee, do you approve
of the punishment?

19:39.061 --> 19:41.862
Ten strokes won't be needed.
I'm gonna do it in three.

19:45.221 --> 19:46.188
Master.

19:47.341 --> 19:49.241
Hear? I'm gonna fix that squid.

19:49.701 --> 19:51.668
And be sure you leave him
looking just like I am now.

20:39.696 --> 20:40.629
The divine eight.

20:41.175 --> 20:43.509
That palm style of yours,
it's really something.

20:44.775 --> 20:46.042
I'm only starting.

20:55.294 --> 20:56.427
I'm not dead yet!

21:17.292 --> 21:18.159
Enough.

21:20.692 --> 21:22.492
You've made your ten hits now, Mr. Chow.

21:24.091 --> 21:26.092
And you said you'd put me down in three.

21:31.171 --> 21:33.038
Snake and crane together.

21:35.450 --> 21:37.817
- What?
- Strike the vital points.

21:40.690 --> 21:42.157
Let's try a divine eight again.

21:54.689 --> 21:56.256
I told you I got style.

22:44.604 --> 22:46.504
Hey, my jacket's getting dirty. Take it.

22:58.762 --> 23:01.296
I bet you regret
you didn't pay for that jade.

23:04.442 --> 23:05.509
You got the wrong guy!

23:11.441 --> 23:12.708
Are you all right, master?

23:14.441 --> 23:15.408
You idiot!

23:27.680 --> 23:31.113
Master, now I look just like you do.

23:32.879 --> 23:34.946
Okay. You win.

23:35.439 --> 23:38.406
Smart of you to play that trick on us.
I'll get you back. Let's go.

23:39.119 --> 23:41.252
You haven't heard the last of this.
Let's get out of here.

23:41.758 --> 23:44.058
Careful with my son. I'll get you yet!

23:44.598 --> 23:45.965
I didn't know your son could fly.

23:47.357 --> 23:49.057
Careful, careful.

23:49.477 --> 23:51.077
He came in a furor
with one ragged cripple.

23:51.477 --> 23:54.011
He left in a furor
with two on the stretcher.

23:55.797 --> 23:58.064
You fight quite well.
I must give you credit.

23:58.677 --> 24:00.410
- But I'll still kill you!
- Oh, no.

24:01.756 --> 24:03.723
You mustn't kill a child of your blood.

24:04.277 --> 24:06.077
Break his wicked ways through practice.

24:06.596 --> 24:08.830
I've tried everything
with that young bastard. Right!

24:09.396 --> 24:11.563
From now on, you won't be allowed
to leave this house.

24:12.236 --> 24:14.303
We'll start with five hours horse stance.

24:59.791 --> 25:00.624
Cold.

25:02.190 --> 25:03.490
Now, don't move.

25:05.150 --> 25:06.550
Have some more water.

25:10.110 --> 25:11.010
There.

25:13.550 --> 25:16.283
Hey, your horse's stance is improving.

25:20.429 --> 25:22.762
Are your legs a bit shaky? They aching?

25:23.549 --> 25:27.049
You know, I feel real sorry for you.
Chicken, chicken!

25:37.467 --> 25:39.001
I bet you this will tickle.

25:44.187 --> 25:46.287
Stop. Don't do that.

25:46.787 --> 25:48.353
Just what exactly are you trying to do?

25:48.786 --> 25:52.120
Carrying out my orders.
See, it's your father's idea.

25:52.866 --> 25:54.733
He says for every bowl you break...

25:55.185 --> 25:57.419
...you stay another hour, you bastard!

26:08.545 --> 26:09.978
Darned idiot.

26:46.021 --> 26:46.955
Master.

26:53.060 --> 26:55.361
Yes, his stance appears
to be pretty steady.

26:55.980 --> 26:57.680
- You're sure he hasn't had a test?
- Oh, no.

26:58.100 --> 27:00.000
I've been watching him just like a hawk.

27:00.460 --> 27:02.060
- Absolutely not.
- You're certain?

27:03.379 --> 27:05.179
- Well, you have problems?
- Sure.

27:05.780 --> 27:07.613
I feel very tired.

27:08.419 --> 27:10.419
- Tired? You don't seem to be.
- I am, sir.

27:11.139 --> 27:13.439
You mean you're tired,
though you're sitting on a chair?

27:14.538 --> 27:16.738
What? Sitting on a chair? Let me see.

27:17.258 --> 27:19.125
Oh, my God! So he is! On a chair!

27:20.137 --> 27:21.371
You young criminal.

27:22.098 --> 27:23.765
