01:03:17.892 --> 01:03:18.926
Play.

01:03:20.692 --> 01:03:21.792
You win!

01:03:23.731 --> 01:03:26.732
We've won again!
We've got it right on! This is great!

01:03:28.091 --> 01:03:29.425
I told you he would.

01:03:32.211 --> 01:03:34.311
We've got enough
to buy a decent meal and good wine.

01:03:34.811 --> 01:03:36.277
- We're rich!
- Hey, you there.

01:03:36.770 --> 01:03:40.404
Old man. I've got 50 to lose.
I'll play you for it.

01:03:41.410 --> 01:03:42.310
Right.

01:03:42.770 --> 01:03:44.103
This should be good.

01:04:08.927 --> 01:04:11.194
- Go ahead, choose.
- Oh, sure, sit.

01:04:17.247 --> 01:04:18.214
Let's see.

01:04:29.485 --> 01:04:30.952
You see? It's not there.

01:04:31.325 --> 01:04:33.059
- Hold on.
- Hey, what the...

01:04:33.485 --> 01:04:36.318
You think you're quick, huh?
Listen, baldy, my eyes are quicker.

01:04:38.084 --> 01:04:38.984
Lay off!

01:04:41.724 --> 01:04:43.624
You're trying to cheat, huh?

01:04:46.643 --> 01:04:48.643
Police! Police!

01:04:49.483 --> 01:04:50.950
Hey, everybody, run! Let's go!

01:04:58.683 --> 01:05:00.516
You're a dishonest cheat and a dirty thief.

01:05:00.962 --> 01:05:02.562
- Give me back that money!
- Nah!

01:05:03.002 --> 01:05:05.402
You must be joking.
I ain't got no money, you meathead.

01:05:05.962 --> 01:05:08.129
- Don't you recognize who I am?
- Who cares who you are!

01:05:08.761 --> 01:05:11.062
That's right.
And I'll tell you who you're talking to.

01:05:11.601 --> 01:05:13.135
Rat, the Iron-Headed Bullet.

01:05:17.441 --> 01:05:19.107
Oh, wow. That's horrible.

01:05:20.321 --> 01:05:21.421
Scared, are you?

01:05:22.400 --> 01:05:25.334
Hey, baldy! You'd better get this straight.

01:05:26.080 --> 01:05:28.714
You're gonna pay back that money.
I don't care if you're a tiger!

01:05:30.040 --> 01:05:31.473
I warn you, shitface.

01:05:31.840 --> 01:05:33.940
I pick who I'm gonna bury next.

01:05:34.679 --> 01:05:37.346
Say your prayers fast,
'cause you're about to feel my iron head!

01:05:57.557 --> 01:06:00.157
- Teacher, his head's much too hard.
- Don't give up now.

01:06:00.957 --> 01:06:02.790
Let's see how you stop Iron-Bullet!

01:06:25.635 --> 01:06:26.935
Good. Very good.

01:06:53.151 --> 01:06:54.385
You sure can jump.

01:06:54.791 --> 01:06:56.524
Bet you'd never guess
that's how you'd end up...

01:06:57.151 --> 01:06:58.251
...jumping into someone's pants.

01:06:58.551 --> 01:06:59.551
Why, you...

01:07:26.788 --> 01:07:29.189
Great! It works! Here, hard nut, try this!

01:07:32.747 --> 01:07:35.448
Gong! You still feel like fighting, huh?

01:07:42.027 --> 01:07:43.027
Good boy. Go.

01:07:44.227 --> 01:07:45.327
I missed!

01:07:47.106 --> 01:07:47.940
Again.

01:07:51.786 --> 01:07:53.586
Looks like your bullet's got carbuncles.

01:07:56.105 --> 01:07:57.372
That's enough, please!

01:07:58.105 --> 01:07:59.005
Sure.

01:08:14.864 --> 01:08:16.564
Teacher, my wrists are killing me!

01:08:32.301 --> 01:08:33.535
Get up!

01:08:34.942 --> 01:08:38.408
One, two, three, four, five, six...

01:08:39.220 --> 01:08:40.787
Oh, my hands!

01:08:49.819 --> 01:08:51.987
No more exercises.
Go fetch some wine from the village.

01:08:52.500 --> 01:08:54.500
Oh, sure. Okay, teacher.

01:09:05.939 --> 01:09:06.906
Waiter!

01:09:09.578 --> 01:09:11.979
- Some more wine in there.
- How much wine, sir?

01:09:13.298 --> 01:09:15.165
Fill the bottle with 3 cups.
That should be enough.

01:09:15.738 --> 01:09:17.238
Red wine or white, sir?

01:09:17.898 --> 01:09:19.764
White wine, you idiot! Be quick!

01:09:25.176 --> 01:09:25.877
Sir?

01:09:26.096 --> 01:09:26.930
Put it down.

01:09:35.935 --> 01:09:36.937
Sure. Yeah.

01:09:47.654 --> 01:09:48.622
Damn it!

01:09:49.934 --> 01:09:52.600
Where's that stupid boy got to
with my wine?

01:10:02.254 --> 01:10:03.287
Where is he?

01:10:09.533 --> 01:10:10.667
That's the fella.

01:10:17.972 --> 01:10:21.239
- Old man, where are you from?
- And who may you be?

01:10:24.251 --> 01:10:27.818
Old man, have you ever heard
of the name King of Bamboo?

01:10:28.851 --> 01:10:30.851
Yes, of course I have.

01:10:31.770 --> 01:10:34.104
I have no doubt So Hai rings a little bell?

01:10:35.050 --> 01:10:36.150
So Hai?

01:10:37.131 --> 01:10:38.464
I and no other.

01:10:40.530 --> 01:10:42.830
- Let's get out of here.
- But hold it, Bamboo.

01:10:43.370 --> 01:10:45.104
- You don't believe that's So Hai?
- Why not?

01:10:45.529 --> 01:10:46.863
See there? His hands.

01:10:48.889 --> 01:10:51.223
So Hai wouldn't be shaking like that,
would he?

01:10:51.809 --> 01:10:53.143
You can see he's a fake.

01:10:58.008 --> 01:11:01.609
Got it. You think you're being funny?
But I ain't taken in so easy.

01:11:02.767 --> 01:11:05.068
But I'm not lying to you.
After all, I am So Hai.

01:11:05.928 --> 01:11:06.995
Well, let's see.

01:11:59.123 --> 01:12:00.623
- Teacher!
- Give me the wine!

01:12:11.002 --> 01:12:12.068
It's water!

01:12:18.841 --> 01:12:20.674
You idiot! Now see what you've done.

01:12:29.920 --> 01:12:30.987
Teacher!

01:12:51.398 --> 01:12:52.431
This way!

01:13:24.354 --> 01:13:25.854
So, they were damn lucky.

01:13:26.594 --> 01:13:28.861
Next time I see them
I shall take them apart.

01:13:29.594 --> 01:13:30.461
Let's go.

01:13:54.272 --> 01:13:56.405
That's bad. You must eat after a fight.

01:13:58.071 --> 01:14:01.138
Teacher, you know I'm sorry.
It was all because I spent the money.

01:14:01.831 --> 01:14:03.797
Seems bad luck follows you around.

01:14:04.670 --> 01:14:07.204
I have seen a lot of things
in these past 70 years.

01:14:07.830 --> 01:14:10.730
But till today, I can honestly say
I've never been beaten in a fight.

01:14:11.390 --> 01:14:13.024
It wasn't that Bamboo
was better than you.

01:14:13.429 --> 01:14:15.696
It's because you've got no strength
without your wine.

01:14:16.350 --> 01:14:18.117
You sure can talk.

01:14:19.349 --> 01:14:21.083
It's true. But if I wasn't so badly trained...

01:14:21.509 --> 01:14:24.076
...I could've beat that no-good jerk,
even though he's Bamboo King.

01:14:25.668 --> 01:14:27.668
You mean to say
you think I'm not teaching you right?

01:14:28.148 --> 01:14:29.282
Is that it?

01:14:29.908 --> 01:14:32.241
Well, it's all exercise.
Just falling all over the ground.

01:14:32.788 --> 01:14:34.788
Boring wrist exercises.
How could I win with that?

01:14:41.707 --> 01:14:43.341
Don't you realize your father is...

01:14:43.746 --> 01:14:45.547
...without question, a real good teacher?

01:14:45.986 --> 01:14:48.453
Robert Wong's methods
are some of the best there are.

01:14:49.066 --> 01:14:51.566
So why do you think he asked me
to teach you my style?

01:14:52.466 --> 01:14:54.433
Just so you could torture me.

01:14:56.465 --> 01:15:00.533
He wants you to train with me
'cause he knows I've got a secret style.

01:15:02.185 --> 01:15:05.785
- Tell me about it then.
- The secret of my eight drunk gods.

01:15:06.585 --> 01:15:08.418
Oh, yeah?
I suppose you'll probably teach...

01:15:08.865 --> 01:15:10.598
...the crawl of the drunken cat to me.

01:15:11.544 --> 01:15:13.111
That shows your damned ignorance.

01:15:13.504 --> 01:15:15.837
Dozens and dozens of men
have pleaded with me to teach them.

01:15:16.464 --> 01:15:18.231
Always refuse. So there.

01:15:51.100 --> 01:15:53.134
Don't be fooled by my staggering around.

01:15:53.621 --> 01:15:55.187
There's power inside to kill.

01:15:55.580 --> 01:15:57.314
It looks real enough, yet it isn't.

01:15:57.820 --> 01:16:00.387
The fact that you're pretending to lose
lets you win.

01:16:19.737 --> 01:16:21.371
So, clever, isn't it?

01:16:22.577 --> 01:16:24.144
So why haven't you shown me yet?

01:16:25.497 --> 01:16:27.430
You must know the importance of basics.

01:16:27.936 --> 01:16:30.470
Without them,
all your work is a waste of time.

01:16:31.256 --> 01:16:32.790
Why do you think I've been pushing you?

01:16:33.177 --> 01:16:35.210
There are basics that you need
in order to master...

01:16:35.696 --> 01:16:37.563
...the techniques of the eight drunken gods.

01:16:38.776 --> 01:16:40.976
- I think you're ready for it.
- Is that right?

01:16:41.536 --> 01:16:43.636
To study my style you'll find it easier...

01:16:44.136 --> 01:16:45.703
...if you have a drink first.

01:16:48.854 --> 01:16:49.988
Come on, drink up.

01:16:57.374 --> 01:16:58.908
Take another cup.

01:17:04.694 --> 01:17:06.627
Now, Freddie, did you go to school, boy?

01:17:07.093 --> 01:17:09.160
Sure. It was awful.
Real stupid professors.

01:17:12.092 --> 01:17:13.326
Drink down the wine.

01:17:15.013 --> 01:17:17.546
- Cups should not rest!
- I'll sing you songs.

01:17:19.172 --> 01:17:20.905
And it'll put your ears to the test, right?

01:17:21.932 --> 01:17:24.899
"Power and wealth are to no avail"

01:17:25.572 --> 01:17:28.138
"Let only our drinking prevail"

01:17:28.971 --> 01:17:30.738
Boy, enough. Enough!

01:17:34.690 --> 01:17:36.991
"A sober man and the sages"

01:17:37.530 --> 01:17:39.164
"are both lost through the ages"

01:17:39.570 --> 01:17:41.671
"But all our brave drinkers never shall die"

01:17:43.849 --> 01:17:46.183
"But all our brave drinkers never shall die"

01:17:46.889 --> 01:17:49.123
Chen Fong produces wine like this
by the ton.

01:17:50.609 --> 01:17:53.143
You know why soldiers
are always so young?

01:17:56.288 --> 01:17:58.288
"Even the king couldn't stop my drinking"

01:17:59.288 --> 01:18:01.755
"Let's drink a toast
to our ship that's sinking"

01:18:04.008 --> 01:18:06.008
"With uplifted cup, I say to the moon"

01:18:09.247 --> 01:18:11.347
"Why does my shadow appear to swoon?"

01:18:12.486 --> 01:18:14.253
"Wine is ready in cup, you see"

01:18:15.566 --> 01:18:16.967
"Put down my cup"

01:18:17.326 --> 01:18:18.626
"The horses are waging"

01:18:18.966 --> 01:18:22.333
"Fallen in the fields of battle,
the soldier says"

01:18:23.086 --> 01:18:24.386
"Who will remember me?"

01:18:26.086 --> 01:18:27.619
"Who will remember me?"

01:18:38.924 --> 01:18:41.591
<i>The god Liu. The drunkard
with internal strength.</i>

01:19:17.721 --> 01:19:21.188
<i>The god Lee. A drunken cripple
with a powerful right leg.</i>

01:19:47.838 --> 01:19:50.672
<i>The god Fat Han.
A drunkard holding a pot in his arms.</i>

01:20:16.715 --> 01:20:20.582
<i>The god Lam. A drunk with
a sudden deadly waist attack.</i>

01:20:46.953 --> 01:20:50.086
<i>The god Chang.
The drunk with the swift double-kicks.</i>

01:21:17.549 --> 01:21:20.750
<i>Drunken So, the god with
the powerful throat lock.</i>

01:21:44.746 --> 01:21:48.247
<i>The artful god Hong. The drunken
flute player with the powerful wrists.</i>

01:22:07.424 --> 01:22:11.058
<i>The god Miss Ho.
The drunken woman flaunting her body.</i>

01:22:20.383 --> 01:22:22.017
Come on, boy. This is serious.

01:22:23.023 --> 01:22:25.090
This style's meant for women, isn't it?

01:22:25.583 --> 01:22:27.450
Miss Ho is a woman, yes, but she's strong.

01:22:27.902 --> 01:22:29.236
Watch me and follow.

01:22:49.020 --> 01:22:51.854
- Can you do it?
- Oh, yeah, it's real easy.

01:22:52.620 --> 01:22:54.321
- Put some energy in it.
- Yeah, okay!

01:22:58.899 --> 01:23:00.533
This is sissy. I won't do it.

01:23:06.419 --> 01:23:10.319
Mr. Wong, just why did you persuade
the people of Bull Hill...

01:23:11.179 --> 01:23:12.546
...not to sell me their property?

01:23:13.218 --> 01:23:14.585
What was your reason for it?

01:23:16.458 --> 01:23:18.425
Was it because of that business
over your son?

01:23:19.138 --> 01:23:22.038
That's a personal issue,
and it will be settled in good time.

01:23:23.217 --> 01:23:25.184
I'm not responsible. What is your game?

01:23:25.778 --> 01:23:27.178
What is yours?

01:23:27.737 --> 01:23:30.771
Mr. Lee, I am most interested to know
why you want to buy Bull Hill.

01:23:31.656 --> 01:23:33.323
As you wish to know, I'll tell you.

01:23:33.737 --> 01:23:36.904
That old graveyard up there,
it's been haunting us for centuries...

01:23:37.616 --> 01:23:39.116
...disturbing family spirits.

01:23:39.696 --> 01:23:42.296
They'll get more than $20 pet lot.

01:23:42.975 --> 01:23:44.275
It's good money for that land.

01:23:44.615 --> 01:23:46.515
Then you butt your nose in
where it isn't wanted.

01:23:46.975 --> 01:23:49.842
- You mean, you want to buy a graveyard?
- Huh? Huh?

01:23:50.495 --> 01:23:52.795
Don't you believe me?
There's a curse on the name of Lee...

01:23:53.335 --> 01:23:54.735
...and it must be exorcised.

01:23:55.135 --> 01:23:57.002
I've got three mistresses without children.

01:23:57.454 --> 01:24:00.154
I'd be content with a chicken egg,
but they can't produce that.

01:24:00.773 --> 01:24:03.340
Or might you be becoming a little senile?

01:24:07.573 --> 01:24:09.774
Yeah, you like to talk some, Mr. Lee.

01:24:10.292 --> 01:24:12.059
I don't find it amusing, I'm afraid.

01:24:12.493 --> 01:24:14.426
- And what's that supposed to mean?
- Just this.

01:24:14.892 --> 01:24:18.092
You want Bull Hill in order that
you can have what's under the ground.

01:24:19.211 --> 01:24:21.178
- Huh? You must be mad!
- The coal.

01:24:21.732 --> 01:24:23.998
- Bull!
- You know very well that Bull Hill...

01:24:24.531 --> 01:24:26.265
...has a rich coal seam downriver.

01:24:26.691 --> 01:24:29.258
And that's a large interest you've got
in Panco Company.

01:24:29.931 --> 01:24:31.464
Yeah. That's why you want to buy...

01:24:31.851 --> 01:24:33.584
...and I'm going to see that you don't!

01:24:38.570 --> 01:24:39.904
There's a real big deposit there.

01:24:40.249 --> 01:24:41.916
Now, Wong, let's cut you in on it.

01:24:42.330 --> 01:24:46.297
As soon as the deal's over,
I'll see that there is 20 percent in it for you.

01:24:47.170 --> 01:24:49.537
Is that so? I'm highly flattered.

01:24:50.249 --> 01:24:51.849
Kind of you, but I refuse.

01:24:52.368 --> 01:24:54.102
In the first instance, it's not yours to give.

01:24:54.529 --> 01:24:56.996
That land belongs to the people here.
Now you can go!

01:24:58.168 --> 01:25:00.335
Robert Wong, don't try to stop me.

01:25:00.888 --> 01:25:03.488
I'll not be thwarted over this.
There's ways and means!

01:25:22.446 --> 01:25:26.113
<i>I will pay you $1,000
for the death of Robert Wong.</i>

01:25:28.766 --> 01:25:29.999
Robert Wong's dead.

01:25:43.364 --> 01:25:45.264
You got everything ready
for the wedding feast?

01:25:45.724 --> 01:25:47.124
Sure. Take a look around.

01:25:52.123 --> 01:25:54.257
See that there's plenty of wine
at table one.

01:26:00.003 --> 01:26:02.070
Well, it's you again, Mr. Stick.

01:26:04.762 --> 01:26:05.962
Big funeral, huh?

01:26:08.521 --> 01:26:09.755
Are you a damn masochist...

01:26:10.082 --> 01:26:11.648
...coming here,
looking for more punishment?

01:26:12.041 --> 01:26:13.175
Are you still itching?

01:26:16.561 --> 01:26:19.628
Yeah, I'm itching, all right.
My hands are restless.

01:26:20.520 --> 01:26:22.621
Ah, good. I'll break another dish.

01:26:23.120 --> 01:26:25.121
- What's that, sir?
- Filleted boy on stick.

01:26:25.920 --> 01:26:27.187
Go get my stick.

01:26:27.840 --> 01:26:28.807
So, you cook.

01:26:30.439 --> 01:26:31.539
I'll try this.

01:26:33.639 --> 01:26:35.272
Good. Real tasty.

01:26:36.399 --> 01:26:37.233
Master.

01:26:39.799 --> 01:26:40.799
Here's to you.

01:26:42.639 --> 01:26:44.139
I'll have the skin off you.

01:27:12.435 --> 01:27:13.536
Here, bite this.

01:27:16.035 --> 01:27:18.868
Wow! Your teeth are sharp.
Bit tight through the bowl.

01:27:39.233 --> 01:27:40.100
Now what?

01:27:50.671 --> 01:27:52.905
Be careful now, toothy. Take it easy.

01:28:04.470 --> 01:28:06.237
I did tell you to take it easy.

01:28:21.509 --> 01:28:22.676
Sit still there!

01:28:26.028 --> 01:28:27.695
And upsy-daisy.

01:28:30.308 --> 01:28:32.141
And that's called a fart for the Stick King.

01:28:42.107 --> 01:28:45.174
- That's called dog eats shit.
- Not quite.

01:28:51.546 --> 01:28:52.579
No sooner said.

01:30:12.258 --> 01:30:13.392
He's pissed.

01:30:49.175 --> 01:30:53.275
Oh, boy, some good wine.
The old man will like this.

01:30:57.694 --> 01:31:00.394
Teacher, I got some wine for you.
Some real good stuff.

01:31:01.014 --> 01:31:02.480
A present from Mr. Stick.

01:31:06.053 --> 01:31:07.086
Teacher!

01:31:09.333 --> 01:31:10.166
Teacher?

01:31:11.452 --> 01:31:14.719
So Hai, I got something for you.
Hey, teacher!

01:31:25.852 --> 01:31:27.552
<i>Freddie, one year has passed...</i>

01:31:27.971 --> 01:31:30.205
<i>... and the time has come for us
to take our separate paths.</i>

01:31:30.731 --> 01:31:33.231
<i>I have taught you all the techniques
and the magic of kung fu.</i>

01:31:33.811 --> 01:31:36.278
<i>Practice diligently,
master each technique...</i>

01:31:36.850 --> 01:31:39.817
<i>... and remember the eight drunken gods
as the ultimate kung fu.</i>

01:31:40.850 --> 01:31:43.183
<i>My home is the world. Try not to miss me.</i>

01:31:43.930 --> 01:31:45.997
<i>Return home to your father now
and be a good son.</i>

01:31:46.489 --> 01:31:49.223
<i>Just remember, should you ever need me,
I'll come to you.</i>

01:31:50.249 --> 01:31:51.616
<i>So Hai.</i>

01:31:57.488 --> 01:31:58.321
Teacher...

01:31:59.968 --> 01:32:00.935
...don't leave.

01:32:01.208 --> 01:32:04.209
Teacher! Where are you?

01:32:28.285 --> 01:32:30.319
- More straight.
- Master Wong!

01:32:32.004 --> 01:32:33.405
- Master!
- What is it?

01:32:33.765 --> 01:32:36.532
Lee and all his men are digging
up on Bull Hill! About 20 of them!

01:32:37.165 --> 01:32:38.632
- What? You saw them there?
- Yes, sir.

01:32:39.444 --> 01:32:41.744
You, boy, tell my men I'm up on Bull Hill.
Be quick!

01:32:42.324 --> 01:32:43.324
Come on then!

01:32:45.684 --> 01:32:47.817
Ovet this way. Down in the valley.

01:33:19.801 --> 01:33:21.868
Your skill in kung fu is renowned.

01:33:22.600 --> 01:33:24.934
I'd like to compliment you, Mr. Wong.

01:33:26.120 --> 01:33:29.887
Who are you? I haven't met you before.
Why do you want to kill me?

01:33:31.839 --> 01:33:34.939
I'm Thunderleg. For money, I assassinate.

01:33:36.199 --> 01:33:38.332
Today I have an opponent that's worthy.

01:33:38.839 --> 01:33:40.806
I'd like to pay my respects to you.

01:33:42.359 --> 01:33:44.892
